record.title: MILO C. HUEMPFNER DEPARTMENT OF VETERANS AFFAIRS OUTPATIENT CLINIC
record.narrative:
MILO C. HUEMPFNER DEPARTMENT OF VETERANS AFFAIRS OUTPATIENT CLINIC -- (Senate - December 13, 2007)

[Page: S15571]

speaking.paragraph: Mr. President, I ask unanimous consent that the Veterans' Affairs Committee be discharged from further consideration of H.R. 2408 and the Senate then proceed to its immediate consideration.

record.chair: Without objection, it is so ordered. The clerk will report the title of the bill.
record.narrative: The legislative clerk read as follows:
A bill (H.R. 2408) to designate the Department of Veterans Affairs outpatient clinic in Green Bay, Wisconsin, as the "Milo C. Huempfner Department of Veterans Affairs Outpatient Clinic".
There being no objection, the committee proceeded to consider the bill.

speaking.paragraph: Mr. President, I ask unanimous consent that the bill be read a third time, passed, and the motion to reconsider be laid upon the table; that any statements relating to the bill be printed in the Record, without intervening action or debate.

record.chair: Without objection, it is so ordered.
The bill (H.R. 2408) was ordered to a third reading, was read the third time, and passed.
